  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Access to Livelihood Opportunities for IDPs, Returnees, and the Host Community in Diyala Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC proposes to deliver emergency livelihood activities in two areas in Diyala Governorate&#x2014;al Muqdadiya district and al Mansouriyah sub-district in al Khalis district&#x2014;to 455 conflict-affected direct beneficiaries. The intervention aims to support returnees, host communities, and IDPs reintegrate into social and economic structures through short term Cash-for-Work activities (300 beneficiaries, including 15 CfW supervisors), and asset replacement (150 beneficiaries). In addition, cash for work beneficiaries will receive life skills training (CfW supervisors will not receive the training as they are expected to have higher education and skill levels), and asset replacement beneficiaries will receive business management training. The 450 direct beneficiaries will include 181 IDPs, 180 returnees, and 89 host community members. DRC will strive to ensure that 20% of beneficiaries are female, across all population groups and locations. These activities have been selected based on specific livelihoods needs in Diyala, and gaps in the market. In addition to the 450 direct beneficiaries, it is anticipated that 2250 of their family members will benefit indirectly from this action due to households&apos; improved financial situation and capacity to pursue livelihoods. Furthermore, positive economic effects from this project are expected to cascade through targeted communities, due to the overall enhanced capacity of residents to generate income, employee their neighbors, and contribute to the local economy.</narrative>
  </description>
